=== Main festivals ===
* Annual festival ({{ill|lt=June 1st|Q2625|WD=Q2625|1=June 1}}) - On that day, there is a custom in which each parishioner's household offers a {{ill|lt=mackerel|Q8064278|WD=Q8064278|lt=mackerel|1=Mackerel}} shaped sushi wrapped in {{ill|lt=Magnificent|Magnificent|WD=Magnificent|ltq=Q2386378}} leaves as a {{ill|lt=divine meal|Q11591045|WD=Q11591045|1=Shinsen}}, which is called a ``human offering.''
* Taiko (Old) Dance - There is a ritual performing art that is said to have its origins in people who joyfully gathered in front of the shrine and danced after their prayers for rain came true, and it was designated as an intangible folk cultural property by the prefecture in 2001.

